			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p225">Modifying the BEPU CharacterController</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=225&amp;sid=fe9e8ca24108c74be7f44891b726cae3#p225"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=60&amp;sid=fe9e8ca24108c74be7f44891b726cae3" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">nikescar</a></strong> &raquo; 15 Abr 2011, 03:47 </p>

			

			<div class="content">Maybe this would be a good project for Bruno and I to work on together.<br /><br />We need to modify the BEPU CharacterController class to work with planetary type gravity. I'm not sure where to start. I know we need for the character controller to constantly update it's &quot;down&quot; orientation to point at the center of the planet object. If someone pointed me in the right direction I might be able to work it out myself.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" /></div>

			

