	<div id="p229" class="post bg2">
		<div class="inner"><span class="corners-top"><span></span></span>

		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 ><a href="#p229">Re: Modifying the BEPU CharacterController</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=229&amp;sid=fe9e8ca24108c74be7f44891b726cae3#p229"><img src="./styles/prosilver/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Mensagem" title="Mensagem" /></a>por <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54&amp;sid=fe9e8ca24108c74be7f44891b726cae3" style="color: #000066;" class="username-coloured">tpastor</a></strong> &raquo; 15 Abr 2011, 10:11 </p>

			

			<div class="content"><span style="text-decoration: underline">About Bepu character controller</span><br /><br />It is a kinematic/dynamic entity, simple in design (not in implementation) and well commented. <br /><br />Every frame Bepu calls the character method <br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Código: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Selecionar todos</a></dt><dd><code>void IEndOfTimeStepUpdateable.Update(float dt)</code></dd></dl><br />this will handle the movement.<br /><br />It will first look if there is a &quot;support&quot; entity (something like are we in the gound ?) in the feet of the character<br />if exist,  he will discover if he can move (check the angle between the support entity and the character -- the character cant pass some barriers)<br />if he can, he will move. The function that handle this (in the ground) is:<br /><dl class="codebox"><dt>Código: <a href="#" onclick="selectCode(this); return false;">Selecionar todos</a></dt><dd><code>HandleHorizontalMotion(supportLocationVelocity, supportNormal, dt);</code></dd></dl><br /><br />if support dont exist he is flying, there is another function that handle this case.<br /><br />The object is a dual, it has some kinematic entities to handle the movement and a dynamic body to handle the character itself.<br />The gravity affects just the dynamic and it influence the moviment when the character is flying (or jumping ...).<br /><br />I studied a bit the Bepu Character controller a long time ago (in a desperate try to fix the jigLib Character Controller) ... i failed &gt;.&lt;<br /><br />---------<br /><span style="font-weight: bold">MY Opinion</span><br /><br />Its no necessary, we interact with Bepu Controller using a Moving Direction property, we <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-style: italic">JUST</span></span> need to set it right (we dont change it, we change our way to deal with it). (maybe airbone movement needs to be changed, it uses the Dynamic body gravity simulation )<br /><br />the way the physic is, our mech will behave like the mech in Hawken (video in the other post).<br />I think we can consider the planet as a plain surface (analogy to the earth) like them, without major loss. (the planet illusion can be made using skybox)<br /><br />Maybe and probable iam missing something, iam not convinced that we need to make this change. (pls convince me <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />)<br /><br />Iam more concerned about the animation and physic integration, it is always a headache.  <img src="./images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

			<div id="sig229" class="signature">PloobsEngine<br />Creator and Developer<br />ploobs.com.br/?page_id=1381</div>

		</div>

		
